    <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-stone-900 mb-3">Hints</h3>
    <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-stone-700 list-disc pl-5">
        <li>Use <code class="text-stone-900 bg-stone-200/70 px-1 py-0.5 rounded text-xs">datetime.date.today()</code> to get today's date, and subtract two <code class="text-stone-900 bg-stone-200/70 px-1 py-0.5 rounded text-xs">date</code> objects to get a <code class="text-stone-900 bg-stone-200/70 px-1 py-0.5 rounded text-xs">timedelta</code>.</li>
        <li>A <code class="text-stone-900 bg-stone-200/70 px-1 py-0.5 rounded text-xs">timedelta</code> has a <code class="text-stone-900 bg-stone-200/70 px-1 py-0.5 rounded text-xs">.days</code> attribute — multiply by 24 × 60 to convert days to minutes.</li>
        <li>Use <code class="text-stone-900 bg-stone-200/70 px-1 py-0.5 rounded text-xs">inflect.engine().number_to_words(n, andword="")</code> to convert an integer to English words.</li>
        <li>Use <code class="text-stone-900 bg-stone-200/70 px-1 py-0.5 rounded text-xs">datetime.date.fromisoformat()</code> inside a <code class="text-stone-900 bg-stone-200/70 px-1 py-0.5 rounded text-xs">try / except ValueError</code> to validate the date.</li>
    </ul>
</div>

## How to Test Your Code

Does your code work as prescribed when you input:

- A valid date in `YYYY-MM-DD` format?
- An invalid month like `1990-13-01`?
- An invalid format like `01/01/1990`?
- A future date (should it work or should it reject it — decide and handle it)?

